t flexible methodological framework for undertaking a formalist analysis of games. This approach is then demonstrated through a series of detailed examples and case studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aGames. 4aArt and Material Culture. 4aFilm, Media, and Communication. 4aGame Studies. 4aMedia Studies. 7aNON-CLASSIFIABLE.2bisacsh  agame studies, formalism, game analysis, aesthetic theory of games.1 aVught, Jasper, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311102374840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048554232?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048554232zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048554232/original  a978-3-11-102374-8 Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA